<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Continued strong capital position</B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Excess capital above S&amp;P&#146;s AA capital adequacy requirements increases to EUR 3.3 billion; earnings contribution and capital preservation measures were offset
by repayment of EUR 0.5 billion to Dutch State </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IGD</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">a)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> solvency ratio of 205% </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Statement of Alex Wynaendts, CEO </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;During the third quarter AEGON achieved significantly improved year-over-year results, as measured by increases in underlying earnings, net income,
new life sales and deposits. The strong earnings performance during the quarter was driven by growth across most businesses, strict cost control, higher equity markets and the strengthening of the US dollar against the euro. The quarter, however,
also included the negative impact of changes in assumptions relating to customer behavior in our variable&nbsp;annuity business in the United States. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;AEGON&#146;s continued strong franchise resulted in the increase in new life sales within nearly all country units, while our asset management business was the main driver of the significant
increase in deposits. AEGON&#146;s excess capital position improved to EUR 3.3 billion, after repaying an additional EUR 500&nbsp;million to the Dutch State in August.&nbsp;We reaffirm our aim to complete full repayment by the end of June 2011,
market conditions permitting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;During the quarter, we made further progress in restructuring our business in the United Kingdom. We are
similarly on track with our plans for AEGON&#146;s life reinsurance business and will communicate further on the progress in due course. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Overall, AEGON&#146;s businesses performed well during the third quarter and are on track to deliver the benefits of our strategic
priorities.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">STRATEGIC HIGHLIGHTS </FONT></P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">First steps taken in restructuring UK business in order to achieve targeted cost reduction</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">European Commission approves 2008 Dutch State support</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s ambition is to become a leader in all its chosen markets by 2015. This means becoming the most recommended life and pensions provider among
customers, the preferred partner among distributors and the employer of choice among both current and prospective employees. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Achieving this
ambition is based on three strategic priorities: to reallocate capital to areas that offer strong growth prospects and higher returns, to increase returns from the company&#146;s existing businesses and to optimize ONE AEGON by increasing efficiency
and making better use of the company&#146;s global resources. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>AEGON&#146;s AMBITION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To be a leader in <I>all</I> our chosen markets by 2015 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>AEGON&#146;S STRATEGIC PRIORITIES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Reallocate capital</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Increase returns</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Optimize ONE AEGON</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#133;resulting in sustainable, profitable growth.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Reallocate capital </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON has taken
steps to sharpen its focus on the company&#146;s three core businesses: life insurance, pensions and asset management. AEGON also intends to achieve a greater geographical balance by reallocating capital to the growth markets of Central&nbsp;&amp;
Eastern Europe, Asia and Latin America. As part of this approach, AEGON continuously assesses its businesses to ensure they meet the company&#146;s requirements in terms of earnings growth, cash flow generation, return on capital and customer life
cycle needs. Currently, AEGON is in the process of exploring strategic options for Transamerica Reinsurance, the company&#146;s international life reinsurance activities, including finding a suitable buyer. At this stage, AEGON is not in a position
to provide further details. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Improve risk profile </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON has recently further increased equity hedging on its GMIB back-book of variable annuities in the United States by extending its current macro equity hedge program. As a result, AEGON has now covered
approximately 80% of the equity exposure from its back-book of GMIB variable annuity guarantees. The company expects to fully equity hedge this back-book by the end of 2012. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Increase returns </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In all of its businesses worldwide, AEGON&#146;s aim is to increase
returns by increasing efficiency and delivering operational excellence. This will be achieved by further reducing costs while investing in core capabilities and improving service levels to ensure continued customer loyalty. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the United Kingdom, AEGON is taking significant steps to improve its return on capital. AEGON is targeting to reduce cost by 25% in its UK life and
pensions operations by the end of 2011, and is directing more resources to the key growth At-Retirement and Workplace Savings markets, where AEGON has leading positions. As part of this process, AEGON has restructured its UK&#146;s sales division,
has sold its third party pension administration business and is closing its employee benefits software business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Approval European
Commission </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In August, AEGON received final approval from the European Commission regarding the capital support obtained from the Dutch
State in December 2008 at the height of the financial crisis. AEGON has repaid a further EUR 500&nbsp;million to the Dutch State and aims to repay the remaining EUR 1.5 billion by the end of June 2011, market conditions permitting. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="82%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="16%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="middle"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g118695ex99_1pg2-21.jpg" ALT="LOGO"></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">OPERATIONAL HIGHLIGHTS </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s underlying earnings increased to EUR
473&nbsp;million in the third quarter, a significant improvement compared with the same period last year. This increase in earnings was mainly the result of growth in most businesses, strict cost control, higher equity markets and strengthening of
the US dollar against the euro. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the Americas, underlying earnings rose to EUR 376&nbsp;million, primarily the result of higher fee and
investment income, partly offset by charges of EUR 59&nbsp;million related to changes in policyholder behavior assumptions. Underlying earnings in the Netherlands remained strong at EUR 97 million. In the United Kingdom, underlying earnings
increased to EUR 28&nbsp;million as earnings for the same period last year were affected by an exceptional charge of EUR 43&nbsp;million related to a program to improve the consistency of customer records. Underlying earnings from New Markets
increased to EUR 55&nbsp;million as the contribution of AEGON Asset Management and associates was only partly offset by higher non-life claims in Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe and continued investments in growth of the business in Asia. Higher
funding costs and increased expenses resulted in EUR 83&nbsp;million of expenses in the third quarter of 2010 for the holding company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net
income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income increased significantly to EUR 657 million. This was primarily the result of higher underlying earnings, a positive
contribution from fair value items, higher realized gains on investments and lower impairments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Fair value items </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the third quarter, results from fair value items amounted to EUR 204 million. In the Americas, fair value items were positively impacted by lower
implied volatility and favorable equity markets in the third quarter. In addition, the net hedge result was small, as hedge results from AEGON&#146;s macro equity hedge program were more than offset by the effect of favorable equity markets on
guarantees. In the Netherlands, the positive contribution was the result mainly of an increase in the fair value of guarantees, net of related hedges. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A narrowing of AEGON&#146;s own credit spread, in addition to negative fair value movements in derivatives, resulted in a loss of EUR 60&nbsp;million for the holding company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Realized gains on investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the
third quarter, realized gains on investments amounted to EUR 129 million. In the United States, gains were mainly related to normal trading in corporate investment grade bonds, while in the Netherlands gains were primarily due to sales of high yield
and emerging market debt. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Impairment charges </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net impairments for the quarter amounted to EUR 92&nbsp;million and were mostly linked to US housing related securities. Compared with the previous quarter, gross impairments remained at the same level,
while recoveries declined. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Other charges </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other charges of EUR 14&nbsp;million included EUR 12&nbsp;million related to restructuring in the United Kingdom. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Run-off businesses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s run-off businesses in the Americas recorded a loss in the
third quarter of EUR 28&nbsp;million, an improvement over recent quarters. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Income tax </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Tax charges for the quarter amounted to EUR 15 million. These charges included EUR 46&nbsp;million in tax benefits related to cross-border intercompany
reinsurance transactions between the United States and Ireland and tax benefits of EUR 98&nbsp;million resulting from the utilization of tax losses for which previously no deferred tax asset was recognized. In the United Kingdom, tax credits of EUR
29&nbsp;million related to a reduction of the corporate tax rate from 28% to 27% effective from April&nbsp;1, 2011 with consequential impact on deferred taxes. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses increased 7% to EUR 835&nbsp;million due to a
strengthening of the US dollar and pound sterling against the euro. At constant currencies, however, operating expenses declined 1% as result of a number of measures to reduce expenses, partly offset by investments in New Markets. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="85%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="13%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Page&nbsp;4&nbsp;of&nbsp;21</B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="82%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="16%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="middle"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g118695ex99_1pg2-21.jpg" ALT="LOGO"></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>New life sales </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales increased 7% compared with the third quarter of 2009 to EUR 527&nbsp;million as most units experienced growth. The main drivers behind the increase were retail life sales in the Americas,
pension sales in the United Kingdom and favorable exchange rates, partly offset by lower sales in the Netherlands. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Deposits
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gross deposits, excluding run-off businesses, increased 38% to EUR 9.4 billion. This substantial increase was the result mainly of strong
third-party asset management deposits. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Compared with the third quarter 2009, the value of new business declined considerably to EUR 120 million. In the Netherlands, the decline in value of new business is attributable to lower sales and a
decrease in margins, while in the United Kingdom the main reason for the decline was a decrease in immediate annuity sales and margins. In the Americas, the value of new business declined mainly due to lower sales of fixed annuities in addition to
lower margins in the life insurance businesses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments decreased slightly compared with the end of the second quarter 2010 to EUR 405 billion, primarily as a result of a
weakening of the US dollar against the euro. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Capital management </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:0px;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At the end of the third quarter, AEGON&#146;s core capital position, excluding revaluation reserves, amounted to EUR 17.2 billion,
equivalent to 74%</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">7</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">)</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> of the company&#146;s total capital base and above its target
threshold of 70%. AEGON&#146;s aim is to increase the proportion of core capital to at least 75% by the end of 2012. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s revaluation
reserves at September&nbsp;30, 2010, increased significantly to EUR 2.3 billion. This significant improvement was mainly the result of an increase in the value of fixed income securities as a result of lower risk-free interest rates and a further
narrowing in credit spreads. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Shareholders&#146; equity rose compared with the end of the second quarter to EUR 18 billion, mainly as a result
of improved revaluation reserves and third quarter net income, partly offset by the weaker US dollar. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Excess capital above S&amp;P&#146;s AA
capital adequacy requirements rose to EUR 3.3 billion, of which EUR 2 billion was held in operating units and EUR 1.3 billion at the holding company. An additional payment of EUR 563&nbsp;million to the Dutch State was more than offset by the
positive effect of earnings of EUR 0.6 billion and further capital preservation measures of EUR 0.3 billion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During the third quarter of
2010, AEGON&#146;s Insurance Group Directive (IGD) solvency ratio increased to 205%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Improved longevity in the Netherlands </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Updated mortality tables show a strong increase in life expectancy in the Dutch population. AEGON is in the process of assessing the possible impact of
this on its insurance reserves. The company expects that adoption of these new mortality tables will have no immediate impact on earnings. However, higher longevity charges will impact underlying earnings over time. The impact on excess capital
above S&amp;P&#146;s capital adequacy requirements is currently estimated to be less than EUR 250 million. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="border-bottom:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B>The<BR>Netherlands</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="border-bottom:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B>Holding,<BR>other<BR>activities &amp;<BR>eliminations</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="border-bottom:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B>Total</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#cceeff">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax by line of business</B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
<TR>

 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AMERICAS </FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>New life sales of USD 221&nbsp;million and gross deposits stable at USD 6.1 billion</B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Life&nbsp;&amp; Protection in the Americas declined to USD 220&nbsp;million as the comparable quarter last year benefited from favorable mortality
experience.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Individual Savings&nbsp;&amp; Retirement earnings increased to USD 144 million. Fixed annuity earnings rose as the comparable quarter last year contained an exceptional charge,
however, earnings are expected to trend downward as the product is de-emphasized. Variable annuity earnings were negatively impacted by USD 28&nbsp;million as charges of USD 56&nbsp;million related to updated policyholder behavior assumptions were
only partly offset by reserve releases. Mutual funds returned to profitability as a result of continued net inflows and higher equity markets.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Employer Solutions&nbsp;&amp; Pensions doubled to USD 101&nbsp;million, mainly due to strong growth in the business, improved financial markets, expense savings and
a USD 13&nbsp;million reserve release related to the synthetic GIC business.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Life Reinsurance earnings decreased to USD 4&nbsp;million due mainly to an exceptional charge of USD 22 million relating to the changes in variable annuity policyholder behavior
assumptions.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from AEGON&#146;s operations in Canada increased to USD 13&nbsp;million in the third quarter. Earnings from the same quarter last year included an exceptional
charge.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from AEGON&#146;s operations in the Americas increased to USD 628&nbsp;million in the third quarter, mainly the result of lower impairments, improved results from fair value items and realized
gains on investments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Results from fair value items increased considerably compared with the same quarter last year to USD 117&nbsp;million
driven primarily by improved net hedge results as the loss from the macro equity hedge was more than offset by the effect of favorable equity markets on guarantees and a USD 12&nbsp;million positive effect related to the changes in variable annuity
GMWB policyholder behavior assumptions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During the third quarter, trading in AEGON&#146;s investment portfolio led to realized gains of USD
121&nbsp;million, relating primarily to the sale of corporate investment grade bonds. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net impairments for the quarter amounted to USD
111&nbsp;million and were mostly linked to residential mortgage-backed securities. Compared with the previous quarter, gross impairments remained at the same level, while recoveries declined. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s run-off businesses in the Americas recorded a loss in the third quarter of USD 35&nbsp;million, an improvement over recent quarters. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from AEGON&#146;s operations in the Americas also included a tax benefit in the third quarter of USD 52 million. This benefit included USD 61&nbsp;million in tax benefits related to
cross-border intercompany reinsurance transactions between the United States and Ireland and tax benefits of USD 129&nbsp;million resulting from the utilization of tax losses for which previously no deferred tax asset was recognized. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses
declined 13% to USD 472&nbsp;million as a result of lower employee benefit plan costs, the transfer of asset management activities to AEGON Asset Management and expense savings. On a comparable basis, operating expenses declined 4% year-on-year.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life
sales in the third quarter amounted to USD 221 million. New premium production for accident and health remained stable at USD 179 million. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gross deposits, excluding run-off businesses, remained level with the comparable quarter last year at USD 6.1 billion as higher pension, mutual fund and
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
variable annuity deposits were offset by a strong decrease in fixed annuity deposits, as the product is de-emphasized. Net deposits, excluding run-off businesses, totaled USD 0.7 billion as the
pensions business in particular benefited from higher retention levels. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B>Value of new business declined to USD 66&nbsp;million as a result of lower sales of fixed annuities, lower margins in the life insurance businesses
and a change in business mix. The internal rate of return for the quarter was unchanged at 12%.<B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Compared with the second quarter 2010, revenue-generating investments increased to USD 317 billion as new money inflows and the effect of
higher bond and equity markets offset outflows from AEGON&#146;s run-off businesses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>REVENUE-GENERATING INVESTMENTS </B></FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="middle"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g118695ex99_1pg2-21.jpg" ALT="LOGO"></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">THE NETHERLANDS </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax amount to EUR 97&nbsp;million</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income rises to EUR 237&nbsp;million driven by favorable fair value items</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>New life sales decline to EUR 32&nbsp;million due to continued volatility in group pensions market</B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from AEGON&#146;s Life&nbsp;&amp; Savings operations in the Netherlands declined slightly to EUR 51&nbsp;million in the third quarter. Lower costs in the life insurance
business were more than offset by a loss of earnings following the sale of AEGON&#146;s Dutch funeral insurance business earlier this year and lower margins on savings account balances.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from the Pensions business increased to EUR 42&nbsp;million mainly as a result of strict cost control.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-life earnings decreased to EUR 2&nbsp;million as a result of an increase in disability insurance claims and the impact of a severe storm in the Netherlands earlier this
year.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from AEGON&#146;s businesses in the Netherlands increased to EUR 237&nbsp;million in the third quarter. Fair value items improved considerably
to EUR 184&nbsp;million, the result mainly of an increase in the fair value of guarantees net of related hedges. Gains on investments amounted to EUR 35&nbsp;million, due primarily to sales of high yield and emerging market debt. Impairments during
the quarter amounted to just EUR 4 million. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses declined 13% to EUR 179 million. This was the result of a combination of cost savings, the transfer of asset management activities to AEGON Asset Management and the sale of the real
estate brokerage business. On a comparable basis operating expenses in the third quarter declined 12%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales declined to EUR 32&nbsp;million, mainly as a result of lower group pension sales. The current low interest rate environment had a major
impact on the group pension market. However, sales in the SME pension market continue to hold up well. In the individual life insurance market, AEGON increased its market share to 10% in the third quarter as the company is able to sell these
products in conjunction with mortgage loans, while sales for the Dutch individual market as a whole have come down considerably. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of
new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A combination of lower sales and a decrease in margins led to a decline in the value of new business in the third quarter to
EUR 23 million. The internal rate of return on new business amounted to 16%, comfortably exceeding the company&#146;s minimum hurdle rate of 11%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments increased 7% compared with
the second quarter to EUR 74 billion, primarily the result of higher bond and equity markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>REVENUE-GENERATING INVESTMENTS
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Life increased to GBP 23&nbsp;million in the third quarter, driven by growth of the annuity book in previous periods and lower expenses following the closure of the

<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Results from Pensions improved as the benefits of further business growth and improved equity and credit markets were more than offset by the transfer of asset management
activities to AEGON Asset Management, higher deferred policy acquisition costs amortization and higher expenses associated with positioning the business for the future. Also, the third quarter last year included a GBP 38&nbsp;million charge relating
to a program to improve consistency of customer records.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from AEGON&#146;s distribution businesses improved as a result of further cost savings and improved market conditions.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from AEGON&#146;s
operation in the United Kingdom improved significantly to GBP 44&nbsp;million in the third quarter, driven by higher underlying earnings before tax and lower impairments. Impairment charges for the quarter totaled just GBP 2 million. Gains on
investments declined compared with the third quarter last year. Net income also included a tax credit, mainly driven by a GBP 25&nbsp;million positive impact from the reduction of the corporate tax rate from 28% to 27% effective from 1&nbsp;April,
2011 with consequential impact on deferred taxes. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses declined to GBP 102&nbsp;million, mainly as a result of further cost savings and the transfer of asset management activities at the beginning of the year to AEGON Asset Management,
partly offset by project related costs and charges relating to the restructuring of the UK business of GBP 11 million. In June, AEGON announced to re-focus its UK life and pensions business on two core markets &#150; At Retirement and Workplace
Savings &#150; and to reduce operating cost by 25% by end 2011. It is expected that further restructuring charges will arise in the coming quarters. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales increased 3% to GBP 219&nbsp;million as higher sales of
group pensions, primarily driven by market growth, offset a decline in annuities following earlier repricing. In addition, the comparable quarter last year included existing AEGON group personal pension business that was transferred internally to
new group pension contracts. AEGON has decided not to include these rewrites as part of new business reporting as this gives a clearer indication of new premium secured. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new business in the United Kingdom declined to GBP
16&nbsp;million for the third quarter due to a decrease in immediate annuity sales following earlier repricing and lower margins. The internal rate of return on new business during the quarter was 11%. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments increased to GBP 56&nbsp;million compared with the end of the previous quarter mainly as a result of higher equity markets
during the quarter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>REVENUE-GENERATING INVESTMENTS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="82%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="16%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="middle"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g118695ex99_1pg2-21.jpg" ALT="LOGO"></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NEW MARKETS </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax up 31% to EUR 55&nbsp;million</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B><B>Net income up 11% to EUR 30&nbsp;million, driven by higher underlying earnings before tax</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>New life sales up 20% to EUR 60&nbsp;million</B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe declined to EUR 20&nbsp;million for the third quarter due to EUR 10&nbsp;million of claims relating to storms and floods
earlier this year. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s operations in Asia recorded a loss of EUR 10&nbsp;million as a result of continued investments in the company&#146;s joint ventures in China, India and
Japan. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Spain and France increased to EUR 24&nbsp;million mainly as a result of higher contributions from La Mondiale, AEGON&#146;s associate in France.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from Variable Annuities Europe increased to EUR 8 million. These results included a correction of EUR 5&nbsp;million as some elements previously included in
underlying earnings are now incorporated in fair value items. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Earnings from asset management amounted to EUR 13 million. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from New Markets rose 11% to EUR 30&nbsp;million for the third
quarter, due mainly to higher underlying earnings before tax. There was however an increase in losses from fair value items, as a result of lower interest rates and an adjustment to previous quarters. These items have now been incorporated into
underlying earnings before tax. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses for the third quarter amounted to EUR 134&nbsp;million, an increase compared with the same quarter last year due to the inclusion of AEGON Asset Management in New Markets. Compared with
the second quarter of this year, operating expenses were up 6% due to continued investments in growth of the business in Asia. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and
deposits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales rose 20% to EUR 60&nbsp;million in the third quarter as a result of good sales growth in Central&nbsp;&amp;
Eastern Europe, Asia and Spain. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe, total new life sales increased 24% to EUR 26&nbsp;million as a result of strong single premium sales in Poland and continued
growth in Hungary. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Asia, new life sales were 29% higher at EUR 9&nbsp;million as both China and India reported increased sales. Recently, AEGON-Religare opened its
100</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">th</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> branch office in India.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">-</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales in Spain and France were up 14% to EUR 25&nbsp;million as somewhat lower production from CAM, one of AEGON&#146;s local savings bank partners, was more
than offset by sales growth recorded at the company&#146;s other partners in Spain. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New premium production from AEGON&#146;s
general insurance businesses increased to EUR 8&nbsp;million in the third quarter, the result primarily of continued household and motor insurance sales in Hungary. From July&nbsp;1, 2010, AEGON has started to offer household insurance to customers
in Slovakia, leveraging on the expertise of the company&#146;s existing Hungarian non-life business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gross deposits from New Markets
increased substantially to EUR 4.2 billion, the result of new mandates and an improvement in sales of retail funds at AEGON Asset Management. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new
business in New Markets was up 29% to EUR 27&nbsp;million in the quarter due to higher contributions from Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe, Variable Annuities Europe and Asia. The internal rate of return remained high at 34%. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN="middle"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g118695ex99_1pg2-21.jpg" ALT="LOGO"></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="font-size:1px;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments rose 13% compared with the second quarter this year to EUR 33 billion driven by new asset management
deposits and stronger financial markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Market developments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Hungary, the Parliament passed laws that would suspend money transfers to the pension funds&#146; clients&#146; accounts and redirect them to the State budget, with the aim to reduce the budget
deficit. The new regulation is planned to remain in force until December&nbsp;31, 2011. The new law will also open the door for pension fund customers to step back to the public non-funded pension pillar. AEGON is assessing the potential impact on
the current pension and distribution model. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Poland, the Government plans to amend pension fund legislation as well. The main changes would
be a lower contribution fee, special requirements on minimum mandatory capital and solvency margin, and the creation of three pension funds with distinct risk profiles (conservative, balanced, aggressive). AEGON is not in a position to speculate
about the potential impact on its business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>REVENUE-GENERATING INVESTMENTS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Notes: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">1)</SUP></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For a definition
of underlying earnings and the reconciliation from underlying earnings to income before tax we refer to Note 3 &#147;Segment information&#148; of our Condensed consolidated interim financial statements. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">2)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income refers to net income attributable to equity holders of AEGON N.V. and minority interest. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">3)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales is defined as new recurring premiums + 1/10 of single premiums. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">4)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Deposits on and off balance sheet. Run-off businesses includes results of business units where management has decided to exit the market and to run-off
the existing block of business. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">5)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The present value of future distributable earnings on the block of business sold in the reporting period. Value of new business is calculated using
beginning of year economic assumptions and assumptions outside of management control, and beginning of quarter operating assumptions. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">6)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Return on equity is calculated by dividing the net underlying earnings after cost of leverage by the average shareholders&#146; equity excluding the
preferred shares and the revaluation reserve. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">7)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Capital securities that are denominated in foreign currencies are, for purposes of calculating the capital base ratio, revalued to the period-end
exchange rate. All ratios exclude AEGON&#146;s revaluation reserve. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">8)</SUP></FONT><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Included in other income/(charges) are charges made to policyholders with respect to income tax in the United Kingdom. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">9)</SUP></FONT><FONT
